I"#<p>This is one way to use fontAwesome icons inside a placeholder.</p>

<p>In the CSS you have to use this code for the class fontAwesome:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>.fontAwesome {
font-family: 'Helvetica', FontAwesome, sans-serif;
}
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>After that in the HTML you have to add the <strong>fontawesome class</strong> first and then the <strong>fontawesome icon code</strong> inside the placeholder:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;input class="fontAwesome" name="emailAddress" type="text" placeholder="[insert-fa-code-here;] insert email address ..." /&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>and it’s done!!!</p>

<p>You can simply apply the class every time inside your input with the relative code in the placeholder.</p>

<p>And even more, you can use this method by entering the code into a generic element such as a link or a simple text using the same class “fontAwesome” used for the placeholder:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;a class="fontAwesome" href="#"&gt;[insert-fa-code-here;] Great job!!!&lt;/a&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can see the result or read the post from my <a href="http://codepen.io/huckbit/post/fontawesomeplaceholder">codePen</a> post.</p>

